article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- — Eric Sondberg had 16 points in Lafayette's 75-59 win over Holy Cross on Wednesday night. Sondberg shot 6 for 9, including 4 for 6 from beyond the arc for the Leopards (10-14, 9-2 Patriot League). Justin Vander Baan scored 11 points and added six rebounds. Kyle Jenkins shot 4 for 10, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points. The Crusaders (7-17, 4-7) were led in scoring by Bo Montgomery, who finished with 10 points and six rebounds. Kahlil Singleton added 10 points for Holy Cross. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
